  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="ES">Desarrollo bajo del planeamiento de la emisi&#xF3;n en utilizaci&#xF3;n del suelo y/o REDD+</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving livelihoods through the recognition of standing forest value using market mechanisms</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Mexico):  This activity supports ICS Goal 4.3 related to advancing GOM structural reform initiatives aimed at creating more inclusive growth and sustainable development.This new activity will help create the technical, political and financial conditions necessary so that the value of sustainably managed forests can be monetized through market mechanisms. Pronatura Mexico works directly with local partners in approximately 202,000 hectares of forested lands in the states of Aguascalientes, Veracruz, Mexico, Oaxaca and other Mexican states with vulnerable, low-income communities. Additional training will be provided to the technicians in the GOM&apos;s Sembrando Vida to link communities to market opportunities. The activity will train local developers using the Climate Action Reserve Protocol to develop integrated projects and baseline inventories that generate additional income. Also a third party, such as the Asociaci&amp;oacute;n de Normalizaci&amp;oacute;n y Certificaci&amp;oacute;n A.C., will verify and ensure that all requirements are fulfilled, and will issue a declaration and Verification Report. World Resources Institute (WRI) will support Pronatura Mexico in ensuring that the credits increase the wellbeing of the communities involved and are fairly negotiated with the buyers. Additionally, the activity will establish a clear roadmap for the inclusion of forest market mechanisms ahead of the implementation of the National Emission Trading System (ETS) to be considered by the Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources. In order to enable the conditions for the ETS, Pronatura Mexico -with the support of WRI- will review the current framework and policy instruments to inform policy and decision makers and convene a coalition of stakeholders to support these actions. Pronatura Mexico has almost 40 years of experience implementing sustainable activities in Mexico. In addition, their experience with their Neutralizate program makes them key promoting this type of mechanisms.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="ES">Apoya la creaci&#xF3;n o la mejora de los marcos internacionales, nacionales, y subnacionales para el desarrollo bajo de la emisi&#xF3;n y/o las emisiones de la reducci&#xF3;n de la tala de &#xE1;rboles y de la degradaci&#xF3;n del bosque (REDD+). Esto incluye capacidad del edificio de crear o de mejorar estrategias de desarrollo bajas de la emisi&#xF3;n; mejorando los datos y las herramientas anal&#xED;ticas usados para el planeamiento bajo de la emisi&#xF3;n; construyendo o mejorando la supervisi&#xF3;n, la informaci&#xF3;n, y sistemas de la verificaci&#xF3;n; y estableciendo a las instituciones eficaces que apoyan el desarrollo bajo de la emisi&#xF3;n y/o REDD+.</narrative>
  </description>
